<div id='home-page'>
<h1>Welcome to Joseph Brant Museum</h1>
<div class='line'><img alt="Line-sm" src="/images/line-sm.jpg?1457101814" /></div>
<p class='subtext'>Discover Burlington’s rich cultural past and early foundations at Joseph Brant Museum, named after the famous Mohawk who first settled at the Head-of-the-Lake. Housed in a replica of Joseph Brant’s original home, the museum was founded in 1942 and features a large collection of locally and nationally significant historic costumes, artifacts and archival material.</p>
<div class='post'>
<img alt="Lego_bricks" class="post-thumb" src="/system/events/images/163/original/Lego_bricks.jpg?1453392372" />
<div class='date'>
March 14, 2016
<br />
EVENT
</div>
<h2><a href="/events/163-lego-mania-march-break-camp-march-14-2016">Lego Mania March Break Camp</a></h2>
We&rsquo;re Lego crazy at Joseph Brant Museum!  Our March Break camp will feature daily building themes connecting with local history and fun ideas.  Whether your child is registered for the full week or for the day, every day will offer something different.
<br />
<br />
<a href="/events/163-lego-mania-march-break-camp-march-14-2016">Read more</a>
</div>
<div class='post'>
<img alt="Lego_camp_006_-_smaller" class="post-thumb" src="/system/events/images/166/original/Lego_Camp_006_-_smaller.jpg?1453841318" />
<div class='date'>
March 19, 2016
<br />
EVENT
</div>
<h2><a href="/events/166-lego-club-march-19-2016">Lego Club</a></h2>
March Break may almost be over, but the fun continues at Joseph Brant Museum for our March Madness Lego Club on Saturday, March 19!  Builders will work together to create the wackiest structures that they can think of, plus have fun building and playing Lego Pirate Chess! NEW! 
<br />
<br />
<a href="/events/166-lego-club-march-19-2016">Read more</a>
</div>
<div class='post last'>
<img alt="Jb_miniature_-_smaller" class="post-thumb" src="/system/events/images/168/original/JB_Miniature_-_smaller.jpg?1455652231" />
<div class='date'>
April 02, 2016
<br />
EVENT
</div>
<h2><a href="/events/168-the-education-of-joseph-brant-april-02-2016">The Education of Joseph Brant</a></h2>
Closely connected with her book, &ldquo;The White Oneida&rdquo;; this presentation examines the Moore Charity Indian School in Lebanon, Connecticut, a residential school attended by Joseph Brant.  Jean Rae Baxter&rsquo;s research into Brant's education lies behind both the novel and the presentation.  The subject of the novel is a cause that Brant championed; that is, the need for the native people to form a confederacy in order to address their concerns with a unified voice. 
<br />
<br />
<a href="/events/168-the-education-of-joseph-brant-april-02-2016">Read more</a>
</div>
